President Obama will travel to Dallas, Texas on July 12th to deliver remarks at an interfaith memorial service for the fallen police officers. He will also meet privately with the families of the fallen officers and those who were injured. Vice President Biden and former President George W. Bush will also attend, with President Bush delivering brief remarks. The arrival and departure of Air Force One will be open to pre-credentialed media, while the President's remarks at the Morton H. Meyerson Symphony Center will be open to pre-credentialed correspondents and still photographers, but closed to the public. The event will be pooled for TV cameras and streamed live on the White House website.